What do the side effects after the coronavirus vaccine say?
Many people who are vaccinated feel weakness, fever and fatigue after receiving the injection, while others do not feel anything •
Can it indicate a stronger immune system of those who do experience these phenomena, or is it a fundamentally deprived rumor?
While more and more people are vaccinated, the lack of information about side effects continues to confuse and create rumors, most of which are not true.
Is the immune system of those who have developed stronger side effects than those whose bodies reacted less severely to the vaccine, which may prove that their system fails to fight a foreign body that enters the body?
"There are several levels of immune responses," says Dr. David Dvir, head of the initial medicine department in Meuhedet and a member of the Advisory Committee for the IDF (Indemnists Therapy Team), and soothes: "Headaches, fatigue, pain in place, are the immediate reactions of the immune system.
This is how the body responds at the entrance of a foreign body to the system.”
Is there a connection between the levels of antibodies that develop the side effects?
“There is no correlation between the sensations and the development of antibodies against the virus.
About 60%-50% sense the side effects, but about 90% develop protection against the virus.
It was not found that people who have developed stronger responses are more protected.”
“In medical literature, there is no correlation between immediate response to the level of vaccination.
In some experiments where people also received placebo vaccines, about a quarter of them developed headaches.
It is also a mental component - how the person perceives the vaccine, if he expects there to be side effects.
Many of the phenomena that have been happening could also happen normally, but since the public is vaccinated, it attributes the response to the vaccine itself, and this is bias seen regarding vaccines in general - attribution of phenomena that happen near the vaccine and are attributed to it.
According to Dr. Dvir, the causes of the reported common phenomena, such as weakness and headaches, are not yet known.
Regarding myocarditis, opinions are divided.
“There are all sorts of theories on the subject, but it should be noted that the virus itself causes higher rates of myocarditis than the vaccine.
One of the theories is that it’s a strong immune system’s response.”
Is it possible to assess the strength of the immune system?
“When students were exposed to the influenza virus, they showed that those who did not sleep or were under higher pressure were more vulnerable to infection.
Besides, there are laboratory parameters that check the immune system or its components.
When you have a decrease in the immune system, you see it immediately.
People get a lot of viral or infectious diseases.
It's not like anyone's hanging out with a weak immune system and not aware of it.
These are people who come to inquiries because of repeated events of infectious diseases, and what affects the system are banal things: stress, nutrition, sleep.
By the way, we also don’t want too strong an immune system, because it can cause autoimmune diseases.”
Soon MRNA vaccines will appear in other contexts, thanks to the extensive knowledge accumulated about them in recent times.
“There is no doubt that he will be paved for other vaccines of this type.
This technology is tested for many uses beyond vaccines - for oncological disease treatments, for example.
Their effectiveness is that the substance remains very little time in the body - enters, does its operation, and then breaks down.
This technology is not new, but it has received a serious boost due to the very great need for a quick vaccine.
Now, for example, we know that a three-week interval between a dose and a dose is too small, and some vaccine experts say that it is possible that after a third dose we will not need another vaccine in the near term, so it is not clear whether we are going to a vaccine situation every six months or that the third dose will give a greater margin.”
Thousands injured: serious privacy failure on Route 6
Road 6 customers?
Your private information, including full name, addresses, payment amounts and full details of the travel you have made, may have been disclosed •
According to the Privacy Protection Authority, Derech Eretz violated the Privacy Protection Law and its regulations.
After a report that Deret Eretz, the operator of Highway 6 in Israel, conducted a security incident that took place at the company, the Privacy Protection Authority began an enforcement process.
As part of the incident, security weaknesses were discovered on its payment site, which allowed the exposure of a lot of information from the invoices of the members' customers, which were exposed to all.
Among other things, customers' payment invoices were exposed over a short period of time and these invoices included personal information, including first and last name, payment amounts, vehicle location, travel dates and at what time.
In addition, since Derech Eretz has not legally documented access to its systems, it is not possible to know accurately for what period unauthorized parties could access the company’s systems.
In the letter of violation, which the Privacy Protection Authority submitted to the company, the Authority emphasized that most of the companies and large organizations in the economy are required to take a dynamic information security policy, and that with the development of threats and risks, the organization has an obligation to strictly examine the risks that are updated and to act in accordance with the update of the security measures accepted in the circumstances of the case, in accordance with the nature and nature of the database.
As a result, companies and organizations have an obligation to update their systems and conduct risk surveys and intrusion tests, in order to examine and prepare for the changing risks.
In addition, companies and organizations must use an automated documentation mechanism and should be conducted to conduct training for employees, in accordance with the provisions of the Privacy Protection Regulations (Information Security).
In accordance with the findings of the Supervision Department, the Authority determined that the Company violated the provisions of the Privacy Protection Law and its regulations, and also demanded that the company carry out a number of corrective actions.
The company of Derech Eretz, the operator of Highway 6, said: "The issue was dealt with in accordance with the strictest requirements"
